title: ICE: `attempt to add with overflow` emitter.rs

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code Note that this is debug assertion is space-sensi ```Rust fn main() { { let mut mutex: libc() = std::mem::zeroed( file.as_raw_fd(), 0, 0, libc::SYNC_FILE_RANGE_WAIT_BEFORE, ); } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0433]: failed to resolve: use of undeclared crate or module `libc` --> treereduce.out:7:13 | 7 | libc::SYNC_FILE_RANGE_WAIT_BEFORE, | ^^^^ use of undeclared crate or module `libc` error[E0412]: cannot find type `libc` in this scope --> treereduce.out:3:24 | 3 | let mut mutex: libc() = std::mem::zeroed( | ^^^^ not found in this scope error[E0423]: expected value, found macro `file` --> treereduce.out:4:13 | 4 | file.as_raw_fd(), | ^^^^ not a value error[E0061]: this function takes 0 arguments but 4 arguments were supplied --> treereduce.out:3:33 | 3 | let mut mutex: libc() = std::mem::zeroed( | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ 4 | file.as_raw_fd(), | ---------------- unexpected argument 5 | 0, | - unexpected argument of type `{integer}` 6 | 0, | - unexpected argument of type `{integer}` 7 | libc::SYNC_FILE_RANGE_WAIT_BEFORE, | --------------------------------- unexpected argument | note: function defined here --> /home/matthias/vcs/github/rust_debug_assertions/library/core/src/mem/mod.rs:643:15 | 643 | pub unsafe fn zeroed() -> T { | ^^^^^^ ```
